# TableCardView

## Summary

Renders a table-number card: an optional uppercase event-title kicker, the table name in large serif type flanked by stationery rules, and an optional italic `@accent` line, with an optional `@logoUrl` event logo as a faint centered watermark. Like PlaceCardView it is a planner stationery visual — the print sheet renders one as the header cell for each table, so print output matches this component exactly, and its colors and fonts flow from the theme's semantic tokens with Parisian fallbacks. Container-query sizing plus character-count auto-fitting of the name let it scale from an isolated card down to a print-sheet cell.

## Import

```js
import { TableCardView } from '../components/card-views';
```

## Template Usage

As rendered on the planner's print sheet (all args optional; the name falls back to "Table"):

```gjs
<TableCardView
  @eventTitle={{@model.eventTitle}}
  @tableName={{row.table.name}}
  @logoUrl={{this.eventLogoURL}}
/>
```
